com.sun.enterprise.server.logging

Interface LogEvent

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LogEventImpl, ParsedLogRecord

    public interface LogEvent
    Event describing a log record being written to the log file. This event is issued from the GFFileHandler. Interested parties may register a LogEventListener with the GFFileHandler instance. The GFFileHandler instance may be injected using hk2 mechanisms to get a reference which can be used to register a LogEventListener.
